data.title: WWE star Hulk Hogan reveals he is engaged to yoga instructor Sky Daily, says ‘she was crazy enough to say yes’; Details here
data.meta_description: Hulk Hogan has said that he is now engaged. His fiancée's name is Sky Daily and the couple got engaged last week, he told TMZ Sportz.
data.text:
Synopsis

Hulk Hogan has said that he is now engaged. His fiancée's name is Sky Daily and the couple got engaged last week, he told TMZ Sportz.

WWE star Terry Gene Bollea, known as Hulk Hogan, recently made an exciting announcement to his fans. He revealed that he proposed to yoga instructor Sky Daily, and she happily accepted his proposal. Hogan expressed his excitement, stating, "She was crazy enough to say yes, brother."

Pro wrestling icon, Hulk Hogan, revealed to TMZ Sports that he and Sky Daily got engaged last week. Hogan proposed to her at a restaurant in Tampa, Florida.

The WWE Hall of Famer shared that his fiancée, Sky, has three children, and he has grown to love all of them.

Hogan and Sky, a yoga instructor, began dating early last year after Hulk's divorce from his second wife, Jennifer McDaniel, was finalized.

This marks Hogan's third marriage. He was previously married to Linda Hogan from 1983 to 2009, and they have two adult children together, Brooke and Nick. In 2010, he tied the knot with Jennifer McDaniel, but they eventually separated in 2021.

In a recent appearance on Theo Von's podcast "This Past Weekend," Hogan shared a significant personal decision. He disclosed that he has stopped drinking in order to uphold his current relationship. According to Hogan, alcohol has been connected to all the negative experiences he has encountered in his life.

Hulk Hogan is a renowned professional wrestler, actor, and television personality, considered one of the most accomplished and beloved wrestlers in history.

Throughout his career, Hogan has secured an impressive record, claiming six WWF/WWE World Heavyweight Championships and six WCW World Heavyweight Championships, making him the sole wrestler to achieve both accolades. Additionally, he was the first to win consecutive Royal Rumble matches.

For his contributions to wrestling, Hogan was inducted into the WWE Hall of Fame in 2005. Beyond the ring, he ventured into the entertainment industry, starring in movies like "No Holds Barred" and "Rocky III" and hosting his reality show, "Hogan Knows Best."

During the 1980s and 1990s, Hogan played a pivotal role in elevating professional wrestling's mainstream success. He gained worldwide popularity and appeared frequently on mainstream television programs, solidifying his status as one of the most celebrated wrestlers of his era.
